{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":13116,"record_hash":"sha256:ebc90dfdc7ddf4c80df3664361ab00d0a928a8f215e0513498c8f8ebde73f6c7","timestamp":"2026-05-07T22:16:15.192Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"previous_status\":{\"completed\":\"::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Validate target before transcript work\\\" body=\\\"`--target` is explicit CLI input, but it is not parsed until `write_capture()`, after the transcript path has been canonicalized, read, parsed, and CWD-validated. An invalid target can therefore be masked by transcript errors and forces expensive work before a cheap local validation. A small cleanup would parse/validate the target in `run_from_current_dir()` or at the start of `capture()` and pass the resolved target into the writer.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=39 priority=3 confidence=0.9}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Empty transcript path is normalized away\\\" body=\\\"Relative transcript paths are joined to `current_dir` before `capture()` checks for an empty path, so `--transcript-path \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"` becomes the current directory and bypasses the intended `transcript path is required` error. Validate the explicit `PathBuf` before joining, or reject empty values with the clap parser.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs\\\" start=57 end=61 priority=3 confidence=0.88}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Avoid lossy source path storage\\\" body=\\\"`source_path.to_string_lossy()` silently replaces non-UTF-8 path bytes before writing the GitMeta `source-path` provenance value. The capture key fallback hashes the encoded path bytes, so this scalar can become an unauditable approximation of the explicit transcript path. Prefer an explicit UTF-8 validation error or a reversible encoding instead of lossy conversion.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbut